originalText.text: After a fun night out with friends we came back to get our car at this garage only to wait 40 minutes AFTER we paid. The parking attendants consistently ignored us when we tried to tell them we waited for ALMOST AN HOUR. They then drove our car around the corner and up the ramp WAY TOO FAST and almost scraped the underside. Don’t go here unless you want to wait more than an hour AFTER you pay for potential car damage. If you don’t believe me about the management, look up the reviews for their other location at 110 West End and read about the many complaints of dents and scratches.

originalText.text: Paid over $50 and waited 30+ minutes for our car after repeatedly being told that someone was getting it. We kept showing them the receipt and the time on it and they kept dismissing us. When they finally realized that one of their members lost the ticket for our car, they started getting verbally aggressive with my family. We had an amazing night up until this unfortunate event. They don’t own up to their mistakes, avoid this parking garage.

originalText.text: I wanted to put something in my car. I asked for my car and they said they would put it in my car for me. I said okay and when I came back 4 hours later my bags were still in the office on the floor. I asked why my bags were not put in my car and they said it’s safe. If I knew it would have been left in open I would have waited for my car to be brought to me.  Then the gave me an attitude when I said they lied to me. Oh well calling corporate.

originalText.text: I used a parking app to reserve a spot here for a concert at Lincoln Center.  The process was very smooth.  When I returned, of course there was a line but it went fast and they brought my car up pretty quickly.  I'd definitely use them again.
